      "code": "{\"query\": \"site:github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven raven_channel doctype json\", \"numResults\": 5}",
      "output": "Title: The-Commit-Company/raven\nURL: https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n## README\n\n \n \n \n \n \n Enterprise-first messaging platform that seamlessly integrates with your ERP\n \n \n Install on Frappe Cloud \n \n Website (ravenchat.ai) \n \n Issues \n ·\n Community & Support \n ·\n Sponsor Us! \n \n \n\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\n \n \n \n\n​Raven is an open-source messaging platform that brings your team's conversations and information into one centralized place, enhancing collaboration and productivity. Whether you're at your desk or on the move, Raven keeps you connected on any device.​\n...\nIt's built using [Frappe Framework](https://frappeframework.com) and offers deep integrations with other Frappe apps like [ERPNext](https://frappe.io/erpnext) and [FrappeHR](https://frappe.io/hr).\n\n \n\n## Key Features\n...\n1. **Organize conversations in channels:** Organize your conversations by topics, projects, or any category that suits your workflow. Send direct messages to other users or create channels for group discussions to keep everyone informed and engaged.​\n...\n2. **Craft your messages with rich text:** Easily send messages with formatting, highlights, links, emojis, code blocks, mentions and more\n...\nYou can also find and share memes using our GIF search\n...\n4. **Reactions, Replies, and Threads:** Respond to messages with a reaction (custom emojis supported), inline replies or create threads for longer discussions.\n...\n5. **Integrate Seamlessly:** Raven works effortlessly with other Frappe apps, allowing you to share documents from ERPNext with customizable previews, trigger notifications based on document events, perform workflow actions and, print documents directly within chats.​\n...\n- [Frappe Framework](https://frappeframework.com) - an open-source full stack development framework. It uses Python, MariaDB/Postgres, socket.io and Redis\n- [React](https://react.dev)\n- [Frappe React SDK](https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/frappe-react-sdk) - React Hooks library that we created/maintain to handle auth, data fetching and API calls to the Frappe Framework backend\n- [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/) - \n- [Firebase](https://firebase.google.com) - Push notifications, Crash Analytics and Performance Monitoring\n\n---\n\nTitle: The-Commit-Company/raven · Discussions · GitHub\nURL: https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven/discussions\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: The-Commit-Company\nHighlights:\nThe-Commit-Company/raven · Discussions · GitHub\n\n### Welcome to Raven Discussions!\n\nSort by: Latest activity\n\nLabel\n\n# Filter by label\n\nUse alt + click/return to exclude labels.\n\nFilter: Open\n\n## Discussions\n\n1\n\n### Intergated Raven X ERPNEXT\n\nSelinaVan asked Mar 12, 2026 in Q&A· Unanswered\n\n5\n\n### Notifications for both Mobile and Web Portal\n\npujanthakkar started Dec 15, 2023 in General\n\n1\n\n### Raven X ERPNext\n\nmohsinamerriaz asked Jan 9, 2026 in Q&A· Unanswered\n\n1\n\n### Sending Audio\n\nyahyaoudra started Nov 27, 2025 in Ideas\n\n1\n\n### Is a paid license needed to self host raven?\n\nEugenMayer started Nov 24, 2025 in General\n\n1\n\n### Is there a way to trigger notificaiton based on Value change in a doctype\n\nmoizsami asked Sep 10, 2025 in Q&A· Unanswered\n\n1\n\n### Support S3\n\nxhijack started Oct 17, 2025 in Ideas\n\n1\n\n### Integrate API\n\nxhijack started Oct 2, 2025 in Ideas\n\n1\n\n### Keyboard goes away as soon as I press send after message. It'll be better if the keypad stays afloat(similar to Whatsapp)\n\nAshwinnontechie started Jun 15, 2025 in Ideas\n\n4\n\n### Feedback on placement of Raven Chat within Desk\n\nnikkothari22 started Dec 15, 2023 in Ideas\n\n1\n\n### How to Deploy Raven in a Production Environment with Traefik?\n\nmetalmon asked Mar 25, 2025 in Q&A· Unanswered\n\n1\n\n### Change the opening event for the small chat interface\n\nShakinoz started Mar 10, 2025 in Ideas\n\n1\n\n### Two frappe site and single Raven integration ?\n\nerp-modernspaaces asked Jan 16, 2025 in Q&A· Unanswered\n\n2\n\n### Is the messages stored in database encrypted ?\n\nerp-modernspaaces asked Jan 16, 2025 in Q&A· Unanswered\n\n1\n\n### Raven sent a message that was not shown immediately\n\nalishirini asked Dec 2, 2024 in Q&A· Unanswered\n\n1\n\n### Issue when I install raven\n\nMohamed-Prospera started Nov 11, 2024 in General\n\n2\n\n### Do you self host Raven or use it on Frappe Cloud?\n\nnikkothari22 started Dec 13, 2023 in General\n\n3\n\n### Welcome to Raven Discussions!\n\nnikkothari22 announced Dec 7, 2023 in Announcements\n\n2\n\n### Disable Replies on Certain channels / Bot Conversations\n\nBaaridunNasr started Jun 28, 2024 in Ideas\n\n2\n\n### Raven is a Partner Project for FOSS Hack 2024!\n\nRiyaMathew-11 started Jul 4, 2024 in General\n\n3\n\n### Announcing Raven Community!\n\nnikkothari22 announced Apr 9, 2024 in Announcements\n\n2\n\n### Direct Messages lists only the Active Users and not the entire User List\n\nzaheer-srushty started Feb 22, 2024 in General\n\n---\n\nTitle: UI Breaks when channel name is longer\nURL: https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven/issues/2151\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n# UI Breaks when channel name is longer\n\n- State: open\n- Author: mohmedfasilp\n- Created: 2026-05-19T13:38:37Z\n- Updated: 2026-06-01T12:04:16Z\n- Repository: The-Commit-Company/raven\n- Number: #2151\n\n## Labels\n\n- v3\n\n---\n\nThe UI breaks when the channel name is longer, when the channel is opened\n1. The '@' button is not showing and The scroll bar not clicable, hides when hover\n \n-\n-\n \n-\n-\n2. Three dot and '>' button not clickable, hides when hover.\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n \n-\n-\n \n-\n-\n \n\n## Timeline\n\n- nikkothari22 issue_type_added\n\n- nikkothari22 added label \"v3\"\n\n- github-project-automation[bot] added_to_project_v2\n\n- Referenced by issue #2174: docs: add CONTRIBUTING.md with development setup and PR guidelines\n\n---\n\nTitle: feat: responsive web app · Pull Request #924 · The-Commit-Company/raven\nURL: https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven/pull/924\nPublished: 2024-05-24T15:58:25.000Z\nAuthor: nikkothari22\nHighlights:\nThis PR makes the web app responsive and work across both web and mobile.\n...\nThe mobile app PWA at `/raven_mobile` will be deprecated when we bring over push notifications to the web app.\n...\n**Nikhil Kothari** pushed commit `a66a986`: feat: chat stream responsive · May 10, 2024 at 3:28pm\n...\n**Nikhil Kothari** pushed commit `e1c9dc9`: fix: hide edit channel name button by default · May 10, 2024 at 4:16pm\n...\n**Nikhil Kothari** pushed commit `09f0ba2`: perf: replaced Channel Members Context · May 17, 2024 at 12:12pm\n...\n**Nikhil Kothari** pushed commit `e0fede2`: fix: channel header styling · May 24, 2024 at 3:08pm\n...\n**Nikhil Kothari** pushed commit `1188b72`: fix: add\n...\npopup · Jun 6, 2024 at 2:38pm\n...\n**Nikhil Kothari** pushed commit `cbaaec4`: fix: channel members list · Jun 6, 2024 at 2:51pm\n...\n**Nikhil Kothari** pushed commit `7729a91`: fix: create channel drawer on mobile · Jun 6, 2024 at 2:55pm\n\n---\n\nTitle: Text Messages with less than symbol (\"<\") and greater than symbol (\">\") is auto rendered as HTML element on Mobile App · Issue #2009 · The-Commit-Company/raven\nURL: https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven/issues/2009\nPublished: 2026-01-29T11:51:31.000Z\nAuthor: diptanilsaha\nHighlights:\n# Issue: The-Commit-Company/raven #2009\n\n- Repository: The-Commit-Company/raven | Simple, open source team messaging platform | 667 stars | TypeScript\n\n## Text Messages with less than symbol (\"<\") and greater than symbol (\">\") is auto rendered as HTML element on Mobile App\n\n- Author: [@diptanilsaha](https://github.com/diptanilsaha)\n- Association: CONTRIBUTOR\n- State: open\n- Created: 2026-01-29T11:51:31Z\n- Updated: 2026-01-29T11:51:31Z\n\nSteps to Replicate:\n\n- Open any chat (DM or Channel) from the mobile app.\n- Send a text with a less-than symbol and a greater-than symbol.\n\n- Example: The text `Hello ` will be rendered as `Hello `\n - Renders `img` and `a` tags. Fortunately, it doesn't render `script` tags.\n\n- Before sending, the message is auto-rendered as an HTML Element.\n\nDoesn't replicate on Web App.",
